        -:   21:/***************************************************************************
        -:   22:*
        -:   23:* This file provides evaluators for partial reductions.
        -:   24:* There are two modes:
        -:   25:*
        -:   26:*  - scalar path: simply calls the respective function on the column or row.
        -:   27:*    -> nothing special here, all the tricky part is handled by the return
        -:   28:*       types of VectorwiseOp's members. They embed the functor calling the
        -:   29:*       respective DenseBase's member function.
        -:   30:*
        -:   31:*  - vectorized path: implements a packet-wise reductions followed by
        -:   32:*    some (optional) processing of the outcome, e.g., division by n for mean.
        -:   33:*
        -:   34:* For the vectorized path let's observe that the packet-size and outer-unrolling
        -:   35:* are both decided by the assignment logic. So all we have to do is to decide
        -:   36:* on the inner unrolling.
        -:   37:*
        -:   38:* For the unrolling, we can reuse "internal::redux_vec_unroller" from Redux.h,
        -:   39:* but be need to be careful to specify correct increment.
        -:   40:*
        -:   41:***************************************************************************/
